&lt;p&gt;University College London Hospital are seeking Bank 3 Phlebotomists to join the Staff Bank.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential Requirements;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Right to work in the UK&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum of 6 months experience working within the NHS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work under pressure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to communicate accurately and effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job purpose;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To perform venepuncture and veneole (Capillary sampling) blood collection procedures (the piercing/puncturing of veins or slicing of veneoles, which are both invasive and clinical procedures). Tio extract blood samples from patients in a manner that makes the blood sample suitable/fit for analytical/therapeutic or diagnostic testing and purpose.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in this role please apply online today and attach your CV&lt;/p&gt;
